name: Natalie Palamides
bio:
Natalie Palamides is a comedian from Pittsburgh, PA based in Los Angeles. She's the voice of Buttercup on the reboot of the PowerPuff Girls on Cartoon Network and worked as a series regular on the Comedy Central pilot “BriTANick.” Natalie is a regular performer at the Upright Citizen's Brigade theatre as a member of the UCB TourCo, Maude Night, UCB Digital, and many other shows!

The Comedy Bureau said "you could peg Natalie Palamides as the second coming of Kristen Wiig. We like to think of Natalie as something all out-of-left-field and supremely committed to her characters..."

She is a founding member of LA's absurdist clown group, Wet the Hippo, directed by John Gilkey. She also worked as a creative consultant with the Obie-Award-Winning Pig Iron Theatre Company on a devised play titled "I Promised Myself to Live Faster" which premiered at the 2015 Humana Festival. Her TV/Film credits include Uncle Buck, The Kitchen Sink, Uncle Grandpa, and Future worm.
